-- Turkey's Erdogan Seeks 2022 Soccer World Cup Business in Qatar, Aksam Says
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2010-12-27T09:02:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-27/turkey-s-erdogan-seeks-2022-soccer-world-cup-business-in-qatar-aksam-says.html
Prime Minister  Recep Tayyip Erdogan 
will lead a delegation of 150 Turkish businessmen to Qatar next
month in search of business related to the 2022 soccer World
Cup,  Aksam  newspaper reported, citing the head of the Turkish
Exportersâ€™ Union, Mehmet Buyukeksi.  Erdogan will travel to the Gulf state January 9-12 to seek
business for Turkish companies in construction, transportation
and other fields as Qatar plans an estimated $50 billion in
World Cup-related investments, the Istanbul-based paper
reported. Trade between the two countries in 2010 will be about
$250 million, the newspaper said.  Turkish firms including  Akfen , Baytur,  Enka , Gama and
Yuksel Insaat are already active in Qatar, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
